.TH "lookup_one_len_unlocked" 9 "lookup_one_len_unlocked" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lookup_one_len_unlocked \- filesystem helper to lookup single pathname component
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct dentry *" lookup_one_len_unlocked
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct dentry *base "  ","
.BI "int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
pathname component to lookup
.IP "base" 12
base directory to lookup from
.IP "len" 12
maximum length \fIlen\fP should be interpreted to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that this routine is purely a helper for filesystem usage and should
not be called by generic code.

Unlike lookup_one_len, it should be called without the parent
i_mutex held, and will take the i_mutex itself if necessary.
